[3] Cholera - India (Karnataka)
Date: Tue, 20 Sep 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: NewIndPress.com [edited]
<http://www.newindpress.com/NewsItems.asp?ID=IEK20050920012613&Page=K&Title=Southern+News+-+Karnataka&Topic=0>

The district administration on Monday declared entire Hukkeri taluk as
cholera-affected and imposed several bans.
Organizing markets, public meetings, mass meals and other gatherings has
been banned. 9 patients, 8 in Hukkeri and 1 in Sankeshwar hospitals, are
undergoing treatment.
