[11] Cholera - Russia (Moscow) ex Tadjikistan
Date: Fri, 16 Sep 2005
From: ProMED-mail Correspondent Natalia Pshenichnaya <crane@aaanet.ru>
Source: Site of the newspaper "Moscovskiy komsomolets" [trans. NP; edited]
<http://www.mk.ru/numbers/1821/article61237.htm>

A 29 year old builder from Tadjikistan came to Moscow for work
intermittently and stayed with fellow countrymen who rented an apartment in
the Southern district of the capital. On his last visit, he could not work
at all, as he had problems with gastroenteritis.
A diagnosis of food poisoning was made and he was hospitalized in the 3rd
Infectious Hospital. When the diagnosis of cholera was made, the Tadjik was
hospitalized in the 2nd Infectious Hospital. Physicians immediately
isolated the 2 men and 2 women [with whom] the Tadjik lived in Moscow, but
they have remained healthy.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[When this case was diagnosed is not stated in the posting. - Mod. LL]
